Christopher Emmanuel Paul -LRB- born May 6 , 1985 -RRB- is an American professional basketball player for the Los Angeles Clippers of the National Basketball Association -LRB- NBA -RRB- .
The point guard has won the NBA Rookie of the Year Award , two Olympic gold medals , and led the NBA in assists four times and steals six times .
He has also been selected to nine NBA All-Star teams , eight All-NBA teams , and eight All-Defensive teams .
Paul was a McDonald 's All-American in high school .
He attended Wake Forest University for two years of college basketball where he helped the Demon Deacons achieve their first ever number one ranking .
He was selected fourth overall in the 2005 NBA draft by the New Orleans Hornets and traded to the Clippers in 2011 .
Off the court , Paul has served as the National Basketball Players Association president since August 2013 .
One of the highest-paid athletes in the world , he holds endorsement deals with companies such as Nike and State Farm .